50|$|A <b>reference</b> <b>rate</b> is a {{rate that}} determines pay-offs in a {{financial}} contract and that is outside {{the control of the}} parties to the contract. It is often some form of LIBOR rate, but it can take many forms, such as a consumer price index, a house price index or an unemployment rate. Parties to the contract choose a <b>reference</b> <b>rate</b> that neither party has power to manipulate.|$|E
